From 6bae49a316c9fc984ab419ac2b67e7ad1ccf27d9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Build Verification Session <build-verification@local>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 11:03:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix build: resolve 15+ compile errors preventing clean build

Verified with: cmake -S . -B build -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release && cmake --build build

Fixes applied (grouped by root cause):

CMake build system:
- shape_add_library() called but never defined; renamed 4 callers
  (UI, Editor, Replay, Procedural) to the actual shape_add_module()
- Target name collision: top-level Editor/ exe and Engine/Editor library
  both named ShapeEditor; renamed the standalone app to ShapeEditorApp
- Tools/liveops/{curator,mod_validator} referenced by root CMakeLists.txt
  but had no CMakeLists.txt of their own; added minimal ones
- Win32Window.cpp (uses windows.h) was compiled unconditionally on all
  platforms; gated behind if(WIN32)

Disabled pending real implementation (see PR description):
- Engine/Editor: CMakeLists.txt lists 10 headers that do not exist on disk
  (HierarchyPanel.h, InspectorPanel.h, ArchetypeViewer.h, SpeciesEditor.h,
  ProfilerPanel.h, ConsolePanel.h, SimulationView.h, AssetBrowser.h,
  TimelinePanel.h, MemoryPanel.h); matching .cpp files are one-line stubs
- LiveOps (+ dependent Bots/Discord, Bots/SteamModeration): CMakeLists.txt
  lists src/HealthMonitor.cpp and src/RemoteConfig.cpp which do not exist
- Examples/editor_demo: depends on the disabled Engine/Editor library

Core engine bugs (Engine/ compiles and libShapeEngine.a links cleanly
after these):
- DeterministicRng.hpp: SHAPE_ASSERT_MSG used before Core/Assert.hpp
  is included (worked only by transitive-include accident)
- Bootstrap.cpp: called SimulationScheduler::GetClock() which does not
  exist; actual accessor is clock()
- ArchetypeStorage.cpp: alloc_chunk() allocated with operator new[]
  but stored the pointer in std::unique_ptr<Chunk>, whose deleter calls
  scalar delete -- mismatched new[]/delete is undefined behavior; fixed
  to use matching scalar aligned new
- ArchetypeStorage.cpp: removed dead/unused entity_array_size variable
- World2.cpp cmd_add_raw(): size parameter was received but never
  validated against the registered component's actual size; added an
  assert so mismatches fail loudly instead of silently corrupting memory
- CommandBuffer2.hpp: used TypeOps / make_type_ops without including
  ECS2/TypeInfo.hpp where they are defined
- Mouse.hpp/Events.hpp/Input.hpp: bare Math::Vec2 (a template) used
  without its argument in 11 places; should be Vec2f
- Events.cpp: read ev.button.mod, a field SDL3's SDL_MouseButtonEvent
  does not have; modifier keys now read via SDL_GetModState()
- Input.cpp: .size() called on a raw C array; compare against
  MouseButton::Count instead
- Input.cpp: SDL_GamepadHasRumble() and SDL_SetRelativeMouseMode() are
  SDL2 APIs that do not exist in the pinned SDL3 (release-3.2.8, verified
  against the actual vendored header, not just docs). Replaced with
  SDL_GetBooleanProperty(..., SDL_PROP_GAMEPAD_CAP_RUMBLE_BOOLEAN) and
  SDL_SetWindowRelativeMouseMode() respectively. The latter is now
  per-window in SDL3; Input has no window reference of its own, so this
  uses SDL_GetKeyboardFocus() as a stand-in -- fine for this engine's
  current single-window use, but flagged as needing a real fix
  (Input should take an explicit SDL_Window*) before multi-window support
- SpatialGrid.hpp: SpatialGrid(const Config& cfg = Config{}) -- a
  default argument building a nested type -- triggered a GCC nested-class
  default-member-initializer ordering diagnostic; split into two
  constructor overloads
- GeneticsSystem.cpp: read species.genome; actual field is one level
  deeper at species.genetics.genome
- EvolutionSystem.cpp: fitness calculation silently ignored
  ReproductionState; comment says this was "deferred to Phase D", which
  the repo's own commit history marks complete elsewhere. Left the
  behavior as-is (did not invent the missing logic) but documented it
  and silenced the resulting unused-parameter error explicitly
- SpeciationSystem.cpp: dominant_hash computed but never consumed --
  same "deferred, never implemented" pattern as above, documented in
  place rather than silently discarded

Result: libShapeEngine.a and ShapeEngineTests now build and link from
a clean checkout. Running ShapeEngineTests: 36/37 test cases pass; one
("ECS2 Entity - remove component") crashes with SIGSEGV, indicating a
real memory-safety bug in the archetype move/remove path still to be
tracked down.
